title: Amazon launches Kindle Colorsoft Signature Edition, gets a color e-ink display
text:
Amazon has unveiled four new Kindles and this includes the addition of Kindle Colorsoft Signature Edition. The latest Kindle Colorsoft Signature Edition is the first e-reader from Amazon to offer a colour e-ink display.
On the other hand, we also get second generation of Amazon Scribe offers new AI features as well as new Paperwhite and entry-level Kindle models.
We have explained the features of the devices below.
Kindle Colorsoft Signature Edition ‚Äì The device gets a 7-inch display that features new light guide with nitride LEDs. The Kindle Colorsoft Signature Edition will offer great support for reading comics, viewing photos, highlighting words etc. The device is waterproof and offers 8 weeks of battery life and wireless charging. The price is $279.99 and the shipment starts from October 30.
Kindle Scribe (2024) ‚Äì The device gets a 10.2-inch display with 300ppi as well as AI features. Users can summarize text into bullet points and convert handwritten notes into text. The Active Canvas offers book notes if you change the layout. The price is $449.99 and the shipment starts from October 30.
Kindle Paperwhite (2024) ‚Äì The Kindle Paperwhite gets 7-inch e-ink panel with a new oxide thin-film transistor. The device gets 25 percent faster page turns. The price of the device is $159.99 for 16GB storage and $199.99 for 32GB storage.
Kindle (2024) ‚Äì The device gets faster page turns and offers 16GB storage. The device is priced at $109.99.

title: Dinamarca - Suiza: Dinamarca se impone a una Suiza que acab√≥ con nueve y arranca la Nations League liderando el grupo de Espa√±a - UEFA Nations League
text:
D os goles de Dorgu y H√∏jbjerg en los √∫ltimos minutos le dieron el triunfo a Dinamarca (2-0) en su estreno en la Liga de Naciones frente a una Suiza que acab√≥ con nueve jugadores, en un partido disputado ,equilibrado y con una segunda parte accidentada.
Dinamarca llegaba con varias bajas de peso -Christensen, H√∏jlund- y con entrenador interino, Lars Knudsen, por la baja por estr√©s de Morten Wieghorst, que hab√≠a asumido el puesto de forma temporal tras la salida de Kasper Hjulmand al acabar la Eurocopa.
Knudsen mantuvo el 3-4-3 habitual de la etapa de Hjulmand, pero a los daneses les cost√≥ meterse en el partido frente a una Suiza que ten√≠a m√°s la pelota pero tampoco llegaba demasiado, en medio de las imprecisiones de ambos equipos.
Avisaron los suizos primeros con una buena internada de Rodr√≠guez, cuyo pase cabece√≥ centrado Widmer, que poco despu√©s puso un gran centro al que no lleg√≥ por poco Vargas.
Dinamarca despert√≥ en los √∫ltimos minutos con varias ocasiones: la m√°s clara, una combinaci√≥n entre el debutante Gr√∏nb√¶k, muy activo, y Eriksen, que dej√≥ solo a Dolberg frente a Kobel, que salv√≥ lo que parec√≠a el primer gol.
En el mejor momento de los daneses, Vargas, dentro del √°rea, mand√≥ un gran pase a Aebischer, cuyo remate desde el centro evit√≥ en el √∫ltimo momento H√∏jbjerg, que estrenaba capitan√≠a tras la retirada de la selecci√≥n de Simon Kj√¶r.
El partido dio un vuelco al poco de empezar la segunda parte. Elvedi se durmi√≥, Dolberg le rob√≥ la cartera y el central suizo lo derrib√≥ al borde del √°rea cuando se iba solo.
Contra un rival en inferioridad y mucho tiempo, Dinamarca dio un paso adelante. Suiza cerr√≥ l√≠neas, reforz√≥ el medio y dej√≥ √∫nicamente arriba a Embolo, un dolor de muelas para la zaga danesa toda la noche.
Dinamarca mov√≠a y mov√≠a la pelota, pero los huecos no aparec√≠an y las ideas tampoco sobraban. S√≥lo en alg√∫n tiro lejano se ve√≠a exigido Kobel.
El partido parec√≠a encaminado al 0-0. Knudsen movi√≥ de nuevo el banco, sac√≥ a un defensa y refresc√≥ las bandas. Ni un minuto hab√≠a pasado cuando otro debutante reci√©n salido al campo, Dorgu, enganch√≥ una pelota en el √°rea peque√±a y adelant√≥ a Dinamarca.
El gol no le sent√≥ nada bien a Suiza, ni a Xhaqa, que perdi√≥ la cabeza cuatro minutos despu√©s de haber visto una amarilla y dej√≥ a su equipo con nueve.
H√∏jbjerg, en el descuento, cerr√≥ el partido con un remate colocado a centro de Skov Olsen y dio a Dinamarca su primera victoria y el liderato provisional. En tres d√≠as, los daneses recibir√°n a Serbia. Suiza, a Espa√±a.

text: [Sociedad](/actualidad/sociedad/) La Cavalcada dels Reis d'Orient ompli els carrers d'emocions i besades Ses Majestats Melcior, Gaspar i Baltasar han recorregut el centre d'Alcoi en la 139 edici√≥ de la desfilada m√©s antiga i espectacular del m√≥n Alcoi La 139 edici√≥ de la Cavalcada dels Reis d'Orient ha complit amb totes les expectatives i ha posat el brillant colof√≥ al Nadal Alcoi√†. De nou ha hagut una gran quantitat de p√∫blic al llarg de tot el recorregut des de la mateixa eixida en l'Avinguda d'Elx fins al final de la mateixa en l'Avinguda Pa√≠s Valenci√†, amb el moment de l'Adoraci√≥ com al culminant. La comitiva l'han obert els dos grups de danses, el Grup de Danses Carrascal i el Grup de Danses Sant Jordi, precedint a l'Ambaixadora Real, que ahir va ser protagonista en el Ban Real, tot just darrere dels heraldos i l'estrella de Betlem portava per un genet a cavall. Despr√©s era el torn del primer dels reis, Melcior, acompanyat aquest any per la fil√† Verdes, m√©s tard arribava Baltasar, amb el recolzament del Club Atletisme Alcoi, i per √∫ltim Gaspar, que tenia l'ajuda del components de Solc, entitat que aquest 2024 compleix 25 anys d'ajuda a les persones afectades pel c√†ncer i als seus familiars. Una vegada tots tres reis han arribat a la pla√ßa d'Espanya despr√©s de besar a multitud de xiquets i xiquetes i alguns no tant menuts, han anat a l'interior de l'Ajuntament per a preparar-se de cara a l'Adoraci√≥ sols acompanyats per l'Ambaixadora i els seus pajes reals. La Sagrada Fam√≠lia ha sigut la primera en sortir del hall de la Casa Consistorial per a anar cap al naixement i posteriorment Ses Majestats ha sortit tamb√© mentre comen√ßava a sonar l'obra de Haendel, l'Aleluya. Just en el moment de fer les ofrenes al Jesuset d'or, encens i mirra, des de l'esgl√©sia de Santa Mar√≠a i del Campanar ha esclatat un gran castell de focs d'artifici mentre les campanes tocaven en el moment culminant de la celebraci√≥. Posteriorment els Reis tornaven a muntar als seus dromedaris, Nueve, Arturo i Sult√°n per a continuar en el recorregut, mentre els prop de 350 pajes repartien els quasi 850 paquets elaborats pels paqueteros. Per √∫ltim com a curiositat, el Sant Jordiet, Mauro Abelll√°n i el seu germ√†, acompanyats pels seus pares i germana major, van ser els primers en rebre un xicotet regal de mans dels mateixos Reis poc abans de comen√ßar la Cavalcada en la recepci√≥ de l'institut Pare Vit√≤ria on els esperaven. Retransmissi√≥ R√†dio Alcoi va retransmetre la 139 Cavalcada de Ses Majestats d'Orient. Des de la pla√ßa d'Espanya va contar com va ser l'arribada i l'Adoraci√≥ de Melcior, Gaspar i Baltasar. author: Natashas Kitchen
title: Comment on Panna Cotta with Berry Sauce (VIDEO) by Natashas Kitchen
text:
Panna Cotta with Berry Sauce (VIDEO)
Panna Cotta looks and tastes fancy but is quick and easy to make! The fresh berry sauce makes every creamy spoonful perfectly sweet and tangy.
We love these mini desserts for parties! Some of our favorites include
chocolate mousse, these raspberry mousse cups, or mini cheesecakes. They are elegant and surprisingly simple.
This post may contain affiliate links. Read my
disclosure policy.
Panna Cotta Recipe:
I recreated this Panna Cotta after trying it in the Papa Haydn restaurant. It was love with the first spoonful, but my frugal self didn‚Äôt like paying $8/ serving. I could make 6 servings for that price tag at home! I actually like this homemade version more with the fresh berry sauce.
Good news! This Panna Cotta takes about 20 min to make before refrigeration. Easy, peasy!
What is Panna Cotta?
Panna Cotta is a creamy Italian jello/pudding like dessert. It has an incredibly smooth, melt-in-your-mouth texture like nothing else. The name means ‚Äúcooked cream.‚Äù It is often served in restaurants removed from it‚Äôs cup onto a plate, but we prefer it served in cups topped with berry sauce.
P.S. If you aren‚Äôt able to find the unflavored gelatin in the baking aisle of your grocery store, you probably weren‚Äôt looking hard enough (kidding). You can
stock up on Amazon (affiliate link).
Is this a Make-Ahead Dessert?
YES! Panna Cotta can be made in advance so it is perfect for entertaining! Serve it in wine glasses at your next dinner party, or in tiny shot glasses for a larger gathering (think: baby shower, bridal shower, church potluck, etc.).
Add the berry sauce and garnish with basil if desired just before serving.
Toppings for Panna Cotta:
We love the berry sauce (strawberries, raspberries, lemon juice and a bit of sugar) because it ends up in every spoonful, but you can also top with:
- Fresh Berries
- Shaved Chocolate
- Whipped Cream
- Sliced stone fruit like peaches or cherries
- Diced Mangos
Watch How To Make Panna Cotta:
I hope you are excited to give this recipe a try! Be sure to report back and let me know how much you loved it.
Panna Cotta with Berry Sauce
Ingredients
Ingredients for Panna Cotta:
- 1 cup whole milk
- 2 1/2 tsp unflavored gelatin, (1 packet Knox gelatin)
- 2 cups heavy whipping cream
- 1/2 cup + 1 Tbsp granulated sugar
- pinch
salt
- 1 tsp
vanilla extract
- 1 cup sour cream
Ingredients for Berry Sauce:
- 2 cups berries, divided (I used 1 cup raspberries and 1 cup quartered or halved strawberries)
- 3 Tbsp granulated sugar
- 1/2 Tbsp
lemon juice
Instructions
How to Make Panna Cotta:
- Off the heat, place 1 cup milk in a medium sauce pan and sprinkle the top with 1 packet gelatin. Let stand 3-5 min or until gelatin is softened. Place pan over medium/low heat and stir until gelatin dissolves and mixture is steaming, about 4-5 min (do not boil).
- Add 2 cups heavy whipping cream, 1/2 cup + 1 Tbsp sugar, 1 tsp vanilla and a pinch of salt. Continue stirring about 5 min until sugar is fully dissolved and mixture is steaming (do not boil). Remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes.
- Place sour cream in a medium bowl with a pouring lip. Whisking constantly, gradually add warm cream. Once the mixture is completely smooth, divide it into 6 wine glasses or 8 ramekins. Refrigerate until fully set; 4 to 6 hours.
How to Make Berry Sauce:
- In a small sauce pan, combine 1 cup berries, 1/2 Tbsp lemon juice and 3 Tbsp sugar. Bring to a low boil and cook 4-5 min or until syrupy.
- Stir in remaining 1 cup of fresh berries and remove from heat. When syrup is at room temp or just barely warm, spoon it over the top of chilled panna cottas.
Nutrition Per Serving
If you make this recipe, I‚Äôd love to see pics of your creations on Instagram, Facebook and Twitter! Hashtag them
#natashaskitchen
Make this for someone you love. The flavor and texture are incredible and it‚Äôs a memorable treat!

This has to be absolutely the best thing I have ever made. I‚Äôve been cooking since I was a child and I am now 55 but for some reason panna cotta has always been my favorite dessert. This recipe is superb.
Accidentally I did use two cups of sour cream in my first attempt and, while it was very good, it was quite rich. There was probably not enough sugar in that batch but it was still very good.
In a subsequent batch I added a little bit of orange extract and I used vanilla beans that I scored and scalded in the initial milk and gelatin mixture. It added a nice touch to have the flecks of vanilla bean in the final product. I also used a double boiler instead of putting the milk directly on the flame, adding everything to that before I poured it into the sour cream. It took a little bit more time and effort but for me it was worth it, as I tend to scald milk to burning.
The recipe is excellent as is but I did try a third time with two cups of sour cream (again) and I added a little bit extra sugar (about 3/4 of a cup) and that turned out exquisite as well. It is a very forgiving dish though it is important to make sure that the initial gelatin is softened in the milk and pay close attention not to burn the mixture.
I could make and eat this every single day of my life. Thanks for the great recipes in your blog.
David
